In the HTableClient.putRow method there is a parameter columnToCheck which expects the column name instead of colIndex. To avoid confusion, please consider removing this parameter.
Is the JIRA number in the title correct?
Consider using snprintf wherever possible to avoid corruption especially when the printf buffer is in the stack,

Two regress tests failed, seabase/TEST003 and TEST010. 

For TEST003, a plan switched over from MDAM to single subset, causing a different code path for predicate evaluation. That reveals an existing bug in the LARGEINT UNSIGNED implementation that will go away when all clients support the new data type. Nonetheless, a JIRA TRAFODION-2778 has been written to track that issue. For this pull request, I've added a "known diffs" file for this test.

For TEST010, several plans switched over from MDAM to single subset. The purpose of the test seems to be in part to exercise the MDAM run-time code, so I made changes to the test itself to force MDAM where necessary. So, for this pull request, I've changed the test script and the expected results.
Note: I ran full regressions on this change overnight on a workstation. All tests passed.

Thanks Dave. I am pushing another commit after more testing in my work space. This code seem to be confusing to me too. But, what I gather is that there is a static member variable CharInfo::builtinCollationDB_ that needs to constructed in a thread safe manner and it is dependent on another static const object.
So, I let C++ prologue to initialize the dependent static object and construct this CharInfo::builtinCollationDB_ in a thread safe manner. In earlier commits I had piggy backed on the CLI code to construct this static variable and just tested if sqlci and some select worked fine. It turned out that arkcmp and other trafodion processes require this static variable to be constructed without CLI
